S, Msb, TA,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$afaqN", "text_ar": "شَفَقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is syn. therewith (S, O, K, TA) as being also a subst. from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA_i$ofaAqu", "text_ar": "الاـِشْفَاقُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S, TA:) [it is said that] the primary signification of ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$afaqapN", "text_ar": "شَفَقَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "weakness:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Ham p. 179:) and it is conjoined with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xawofN", "text_ar": "خَوْفٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[fear]; therefore it is not applied as an attribute to God: (Idem p. 722:) [generally] it signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "affection, kindness, benignity, compassion,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "favourable inclination:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(MA:) [or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "solicitous affection"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.:] or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "pity,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "compassion, and tenderness, and fear of the betiding of some disliked"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "evil event, together with faithful"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sincere"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "honest advice."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.)       -A2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$afaqN", "text_ar": "شَفَقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also signifies The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "redness"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Kh, S, Msb, K)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the horizon"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "from sunset until the time of the last"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ei$aA='", "text_ar": "عِشَا=ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "nightfall"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], (Kh, S, Msb, K,) when it disappears, (Kh, S, Msb,) and the white"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$afaq", "text_ar": "شَفَق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "remains until the middle [or rather until a late period varying at different seasons] of the night: (Msb:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "until near that time:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "until near the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eatamap", "text_ar": "عَتَمَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[q. v., generally meaning the same, or nearly so]: (K:) or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "redness that is seen in the sky at sunset:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IDrd, O:) or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "remains of the light and redness of the sun in the first part of the night, until near the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eatamap", "text_ar": "عَتَمَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S:) or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "light and redness of the sun, seen at sunset, until the time of the prayer of nightfall:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M:) or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "mixture of the light of day with the blackness of night at sunset:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Er-Rághib, TA:) accord. to Zj, the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "redness that is in the region of sunset after the setting of the sun:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "this is the meaning given as of common repute in the books of lexicology; and Mtr says [in the Mgh] that it means the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "redness"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "accord. to a number of the Companions of the Prophet and of the people of the generation next succeeding them: but accord. to Aboo-Hureyreh, it means the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "whiteness"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "after sunset,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "which, to distinguish it from the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$afaq", "text_ar": "شَفَق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "commonly so called, is often termed the white"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$afaq", "text_ar": "شَفَق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as in an instance above]: (Msb:) IAth says that this word has two contr. meanings; being applied to the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "redness that is seen after sunset;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and to the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "whiteness remaining in the western horizon after the said redness."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) Fr says, I heard one of the Arabs say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ealayohi vawobN kaA^an~ahu Al$~afaqu", "text_ar": "عَلَيْهِ ثَوْبٌ كَاَنَّهُ الشَّفَقُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Upon him is,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "was, a garment as though it were the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$afaq", "text_ar": "شَفَق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: and it was red. (S.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,] (tropical:)  A garment, or piece of cloth,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "dyed red."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(AA, TA.) ―         -b3-  And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Day."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Zj, M, K.)       -A3-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "i. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "naAHiyapN", "text_ar": "نَاحِيَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A side,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.; or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a remote side"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^a$ofaAqN", "text_ar": "اَشْفَاقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (O, K.) One says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^anaA fiY A^a$ofaAqK mino h`*aA AlA^amori", "text_ar": "اَنَا فِى اَشْفَاقٍ مِنْ هٰذَا الاَمْرِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nawaAHK", "text_ar": "نَوَاحٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I am apart,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "aloof, from this affair;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as though"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "on, remote sides thereof"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (O, TA:) and in like manner"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY EuruwDK minohu", "text_ar": "فِى عُرُوضٍ مِنْهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[app. a mistranscription for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaruwDK", "text_ar": "عَرُوضٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "naAHiyapK", "text_ar": "نَاحِيَةٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fY", "text_ar": "فى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aEoraADK mnh", "text_ar": "اَعْرَاضٍ منه"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nawaAHK", "text_ar": "نَوَاحٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.)       -A4-  And (tropical:)  A"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "bad"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "thing; syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "radiYo'N", "text_ar": "رَدِىْءٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Lth, S, M, O, K, TA: [in the TA said to be written by J with kesr to the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "f", "text_ar": "ف"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; but not so in either of my copies of the S:]) applied to a garment, or piece of cloth, (Mgh, TA, and Ham p. 179,) [in this sense, or] as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "bad and thin:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xrv", "text_ar": "خرث"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":) [said to be] from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$afaqapN", "text_ar": "شَفَقَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifying “ weakness: ” (Ham ubi suprà:) seldom pluralized: (O:) and used alike as masc. and fem., being applied as an epithet to a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "miloHafap", "text_ar": "مِلْحَفَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M, O,) meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "radiyy^apN", "text_ar": "رَدِييَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (M.)"}], "source_refs": ["K", "M", "O", "TA", "S", "Msb", "MA", "Kh", "IDrd"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}